sub_title: Engineering Doctorate (EngD) at Eindhoven University of Technology
summary:
Professional Summary:
Recently, I persuaded Engineering Doctorate from Eindhoven University of Technology, Netherlands in ATES Triplet Systems. I did my Bachelors in Technology in Mechanical & Automation Engineering from Amity University Mumbai. Followed by Master of Science in Petroleum and Mining Engineering from Politecnico di Torino, Italy. I did my Master’s Thesis at Denmark Technical University, Denmark in Geothermal Energy Production in Heterogeneous Reservoirs. Since childhood, I was good in both Sports & Academics and won many awards in the respective fields. My career objective is to work for an organization which provides me the opportunity to improve my skills and achieve my goal.

Work Experience:
1. Opto Electronics Factory, Dehradun, India
• I was an Intern Trainee in the factory, a unit of the Ordnance Factory Board under the Ministry of Defence, Govt. of India. I worked on the Manufacturing & Replacement of the parts of the Tanks named T72 & T90, used by the INDIAN ARMY.
• I also worked on different types of Mechanical Manufacturing Machines.

2. Instruments Research & Development Establishment (IRDE), Dehradun, India
• I was an Intern Trainee in the organization, a laboratory of the Defence Research & Development Organization (DRDO) under the Ministry of Defence, Govt. of India.
